spec:
When a `test` job (written by the test-engineer in the `writing_tests` stage) fails, the orchestrator currently silently skips it with `continue`, leaving the feature stuck in `writing_tests` indefinitely with no notification to the CPO. This job adds proper escalation.

## Changes needed

### 1. `supabase/functions/agent-event/handlers.ts` — `handleJobFailed`

In `handleJobFailed`, after setting job status to `failed`, check if the job type is `test`. If so, notify the CPO:
```ts
if (job.job_type === 'test' && job.feature_id) {
  await notifyCPO(
    supabase,
    job.company_id,
    `Test job failed for feature ${featureTitle}. Feature is stuck in writing_tests — human review required to retry or skip.`
  );
}
```

Reference: `handleJobFailed` is at around line 385 in `supabase/functions/agent-event/handlers.ts`. The `notifyCPO` helper is already imported.

### 2. `supabase/functions/orchestrator/index.ts` — `processFeatureLifecycle` writing_tests section

In the writing_tests → building transition loop (around line 2466), update the `failed` handling:

```ts
if (latestTestJob.status === 'failed') {
  // Check fail count. If test job has been failed for a long time, fail the feature.
  const failedAt = latestTestJob.completed_at;
  const hoursSinceFailure = failedAt
    ? (Date.now() - new Date(failedAt).getTime()) / (1000 * 60 * 60)
    : 0;
  if (hoursSinceFailure > 24) {
    // Auto-fail feature after 24 hours with no human intervention
    await supabase.from('features').update({
      status: 'failed',
      updated_at: new Date().toISOString(),
    }).eq('id', feature.id).eq('status', 'writing_tests');
    await notifyCPO(
      supabase,
      feature.company_id,
      `Feature "${feature.title ?? feature.id}" auto-failed: test job has been in failed state for >24h with no retry.`
    );
  }
  continue;
}
```

Note: The orchestrator needs to also select `completed_at` when querying the test job. Update the query to include it.

### 3. `supabase/functions/orchestrator/index.ts` — select test job with completed_at

In the writing_tests loop, the existing query selects `id, status`. Update it to also select `completed_at` so the auto-fail timer works:
```ts
.select('id, status, completed_at')
```

### 4. `supabase/functions/_shared/pipeline-utils.ts` — `triggerTestWriting`

The function already creates a test job if one doesn't exist. Verify it handles the case where `spec` and `acceptance_tests` are both null (the feature has been broken down but has no spec). If so, skip test writing and transition directly to building with a CPO warning. Check if this case is already handled — if not, add:

```ts
if (!feature.spec && !feature.acceptance_tests) {
  // No spec — skip test writing, transition directly to building
  await supabase.from('features').update({ status: 'building' })
    .eq('id', featureId).eq('status', 'breaking_down');
  await notifyCPO(
    supabase, feature.company_id,
    `Feature "${feature.title}" has no spec or acceptance criteria — skipping test writing and proceeding to building.`
  );
  return;
}
```
